Åmli.label: Åmli
Åmli.description: Åmli is a municipality in the county of Aust-Agder, Norway. It is located in the traditional region of Sørlandet. The main population centre and administrative center is the village of Åmli which lies along the river Nidelva. Wikipedia

Åmot.label: Åmot
Åmot.description: Åmot is a municipality in Hedmark county, Norway. It is part of the traditional region of Østerdalen. The administrative centre of the municipality is the village of Rena. The parish of Aamot was established as a municipality on 1 January 1838. Wikipedia

Åsnes.label: Åsnes
Åsnes.description: Åsnes is a municipality in Hedmark county, Norway. It is part of the traditional region of Solør. The administrative centre of the municipality is the village of Flisa, which is also the largest town in the municipality with around 2,100 people. Wikipedia

Øyer.label: Øyer
Øyer.description:
Øyer is a municipality in Oppland county, Norway. It is part of the traditional region of Gudbrandsdal. The administrative centre of the municipality is the village of Tingberg.
The parish of Øier was established as a municipality on 1 January 1838. Wikipedia

Ørsta.label: Ørsta
Ørsta.description: Ørsta is the administrative centre of Ørsta Municipality in Møre og Romsdal county, Norway. The village is located at the innermost part of the Ørstafjorden, surrounded by the Sunnmørsalpene mountains. Wikipedia

Şırnak Province.label: Şırnak Province
Şırnak Province.description: The Şırnak Province is a Turkish province in southeastern Anatolia. It has a population of 430,109. The population was 353,197 in 2000. Wikipedia

Abu Qrenat.label: Abu Qrenat
Abu Qrenat.description: Abu Qrenat or Abu Karinat is a Bedouin village in Israel. Located in the northwestern Negev, it falls under the jurisdiction of Neve Midbar Regional Council. Wikipedia

Adams County, Wisconsin.label: Adams County
Adams County, Wisconsin.description: Adams County is a county in the U.S. state of Wisconsin. As of the 2010 census, the population was 20,875. Its county seat is Friendship. Wikipedia

Adams County, Washington.label: Adams County
Adams County, Washington.description: Adams County is a county located in the State of Washington. As of the 2010 census, the population was 18,728. The county seat is at Ritzville, and its largest city is Othello. Wikipedia

Adanim Youth Village.label: Adanim Youth Village
Adanim Youth Village.description: Adanim Youth Village is a youth village in the northwestern Negev desert of southern Israel. Located close to Beit Kama, it is within the borders of Bnei Shimon Regional Council. Wikipedia

Aderet, Israel.label: Aderet, Israel
Aderet, Israel.description: Aderet is a moshav in central Israel. Located in the Judean foothills in the Adullam region, south of Beit Shemesh, west of Gush Etzion and overlooking the Valley of Elah, it falls under the jurisdiction of Mateh Yehuda Regional Council. Wikipedia

Agathonisi.label: Agathonisi
Agathonisi.description: Agathonísi is a small Greek island and municipality located at the northernmost point of the Dodecanese in Greece. It is surrounded by many smaller islands and is home to two villages, both inland; Megálo Chorió, and Mikró Chorió. Wikipedia

Agios Nikolaos, Methana.label: Kounoupitsa
Agios Nikolaos, Methana.description: Kounoupitsa is a village and a community in the northern end of the Methana peninsula, northeastern Peloponnese, Greece. It is part of the municipality Troizinia. Wikipedia

Ahrweiler.label: Ahrweiler
Ahrweiler.description: Ahrweiler is a district in the north of Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. It is bounded by the districts Euskirchen, Rhein-Sieg and the city Bonn in the state North Rhine-Westphalia, and the districts of Neuwied, Mayen-Koblenz and Vulkaneifel. Wikipedia

Agios Efstratios.label: Agios Efstratios
Agios Efstratios.description: Agios Efstratios or Saint Eustratius, colloquially Ai Stratis is a small Greek island in the northern Aegean Sea about 30 kilometres southwest of Lemnos and 80 kilometres northwest of Lesbos. Wikipedia

Akron, Pennsylvania.label: Akron
Akron, Pennsylvania.description: Akron is a borough in Lancaster County, Pennsylvania. It is a mid-sized town with two main roads going through it Main Street and 7th Street Pennsylvania Route 272. The town is mostly residential with a number of small businesses. Wikipedia

Aichach-Friedberg.label: Aichach-Friedberg
Aichach-Friedberg.description: Aichach-Friedberg is a district in Bavaria, Germany. It is bounded by the districts of Augsburg, Donau-Ries, Neuburg-Schrobenhausen, Pfaffenhofen, Dachau, Fürstenfeldbruck and Landsberg, as well as by the city of Augsburg. Wikipedia

Alachua County, Florida.label: Alachua County
Alachua County, Florida.description: Alachua County is a county located in the U.S. state of Florida. As of the 2010 United States Census, the population of the county is 247,336. Wikipedia

Al-Sayyid.label: al-Sayyid
Al-Sayyid.description: al-Sayyid or al-Sayed is a Bedouin village in Israel. Located in the Negev desert between Arad and Beersheba and just south of Hura, it falls under the jurisdiction of al-Kasom Regional Council. In 2011 the village's population was 3,109. Wikipedia

Aleh Negev.label: Aleh Negev
Aleh Negev.description: Aleh Negev is a rehabilitation village for disabled children and adults in southern Israel. Located near Ofakim and covering 25 acres, it falls under the jurisdiction of Merhavim Regional Council. Wikipedia

Alcorn County, Mississippi.label: Alcorn County
Alcorn County, Mississippi.description: Alcorn County is a county located in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2010 census, the population was 37,057. It is named in honor of Governor James L. Alcorn. Its county seat is Corinth. Wikipedia

Alei Zahav.label: Alei Zahav
Alei Zahav.description: Alei Zahav is a communal village and an Israeli settlement located on the western edge of the northern West Bank, about 20 km east of Tel Aviv, and overlooking Israel's main Ben Gurion International Airport. Wikipedia

Alger County, Michigan.label: Alger County
Alger County, Michigan.description: Alger County is a county in the Upper Peninsula in the U.S. state of Michigan. As of the 2010 census, the population was 9,601. Its county seat is Munising. The Pictured Rocks National Lakeshore is located within the county. Wikipedia

Alcona County, Michigan.label: Alcona County
Alcona County, Michigan.description: Alcona County is a county of the U.S. state of Michigan. As of the 2010 census, the population was 10,942. Its county seat is Harrisville. Alphabetically it is the first county in Michigan, as its flag states "First of 83". Wikipedia

Aleutians East Borough, Alaska.label: Aleutians East Borough
Aleutians East Borough, Alaska.description: Aleutians East Borough is a 2nd class borough located in the U.S. state of Alaska. The borough seat is Sand Point. As of the 2010 census the borough had a population of 3,141. Wikipedia

Almon, Mateh Binyamin.label: Almon, Mateh Binyamin
Almon, Mateh Binyamin.description: Almon, also known as Anatot, is a communal Israeli settlement in the West Bank. Located near Jerusalem, it falls under the jurisdiction of the Mateh Binyamin Regional Council. In 2011 it had a population of 1,033. Wikipedia

Alon Shvut.label: Alon Shvut
Alon Shvut.description: Alon Shvut is an Israeli settlement located southwest of Jerusalem, one kilometer northeast of Kfar Etzion, in the West Bank. Wikipedia

Altenkirchen (district).label: Altenkirchen
Altenkirchen (district).description: Altenkirchen is a district in Rhineland-Palatinate, Germany. It is bounded by the North Rhine-Westphalian districts Rhein-Sieg, Oberbergischer Kreis, Olpe and Siegen-Wittgenstein, and the districts of Westerwaldkreis and Neuwied. Wikipedia

Altenburger Land.label: Altenburger Land
Altenburger Land.description: Altenburger Land is a district in Thuringia, Germany. It is bounded by the district of Greiz, the Burgenlandkreis, and the districts Leipziger Land, Mittweida, Chemnitzer Land, Zwickauer Land in Saxony. Wikipedia

Alstahaug.label: Alstahaug
Alstahaug.description: Alstahaug is a municipality in Nordland county, Norway. It is part of the Helgeland region. The administrative centre of the municipality is the town of Sandnessjøen. Other villages in Alstahaug include Søvika and Tjøtta. Wikipedia

Amasya Province.label: Amasya Province
Amasya Province.description: Amasya Province is a province of Turkey, situated on the Yeşil River in the Black Sea Region to the north of the country. Area 5,520 km². Population 334,786. Wikipedia

Amberg-Sulzbach.label: Amberg-Sulzbach
Amberg-Sulzbach.description: Amberg-Sulzbach is a district in Bavaria, Germany. It surrounds but does not include the city of Amberg. It is bounded by the districts of Neustadt, Schwandorf, Neumarkt, Nürnberger Land and Bayreuth. Wikipedia

Amir, Israel.label: Amir, Israel
Amir, Israel.description: Amir is a kibbutz in northern Israel. Located in the Finger of the Galilee near Kiryat Shmona, it falls under the jurisdiction of Upper Galilee Regional Council. In 2011 it had a population of 536. Wikipedia

Amite County, Mississippi.label: Amite County
Amite County, Mississippi.description: Amite County is a county located in the state of Mississippi. As of the 2010 census, the population was 12,131. It is named after the Amite River which is located in the county. The name is derived from the French amitié, meaning "friendship." Wikipedia

Ammerland.label: Ammerland
Ammerland.description: Ammerland is a district in Lower Saxony, Germany. It is bounded by the city of Oldenburg and the districts of Oldenburg, Cloppenburg, Leer, Friesland and Wesermarsch. Wikipedia

Anderson County, Texas.label: Anderson County
Anderson County, Texas.description: Anderson County is a county located in the U.S. state of Texas. As of the 2010 census, the population was 58,458. Its county seat is Palestine. Wikipedia

Androscoggin County, Maine.label: Androscoggin County
Androscoggin County, Maine.description: Androscoggin County is a county located in the U.S. state of Maine. As of the 2010 U.S. census, the county's population was 107,702. Its county seat is Auburn. Wikipedia
Colleges and Universities: Central Maine Medical Center School of Radiologic Technology
Central Maine Medical Center College of Nursing and Health Professions

Anhalt-Bitterfeld.label: Anhalt-Bitterfeld
Anhalt-Bitterfeld.description: Anhalt-Bitterfeld is a district in Saxony-Anhalt, Germany. Its capital is Köthen. Wikipedia

Anoka County, Minnesota.label: Anoka County
Anoka County, Minnesota.description: Anoka County is the fourth-most populous county in the U.S. state of Minnesota. As of the 2010 census, Anoka County's population was 330,844.The county seat and namesake of the county is the City of ... Wikipedia

Anne Arundel County, Maryland.label: Anne Arundel County
Anne Arundel County, Maryland.description: Anne Arundel County is a county located in the U.S. state of Maryland. As of the 2010 census, its population was 537,656, a population increase of just under 10% since 2000. Its county seat is Annapolis, which is also the capital of the state. Wikipedia

Ano Fanari.label: Ano Fanari
Ano Fanari.description: Ano Fanari is a mountain village in the Troizina area, northeastern Peloponnese, Greece. A small acropolis rises above Ano Fanari. It is situated on the old road from Galatas to Agia Eleni and Epidavros. Wikipedia

Anson County, North Carolina.label: Anson County
Anson County, North Carolina.description: Anson County is a county located in the U.S. state of North Carolina. As of the 2010 census, the population was 26,948. Its county seat is Wadesboro. Wikipedia

Antelope County, Nebraska.label: Antelope County
Antelope County, Nebraska.description: Antelope County is a county located in the U.S. state of Nebraska, and was formed in 1871. As of the 2010 census, the population was 6,685. Its county seat is Neligh. The Ashfall Fossil Beds National Natural Landmark is located within the county. Wikipedia

Appling County, Georgia.label: Appling County
Appling County, Georgia.description: Appling County is a county located in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2010 census, the population was 18,236. The county seat is Baxley. Wikipedia

Aroostook County, Maine.label: Aroostook County
Aroostook County, Maine.description: Aroostook County is a county located in the U.S. state of Maine. As of the 2010 census, the population was 71,870. Its seat is Houlton. Wikipedia

Arkansas County, Arkansas.label: Arkansas County
Arkansas County, Arkansas.description: Arkansas County is a county located in the U.S. state of Arkansas. As of the 2010 census, the population was 19,019. The county has two county seats, De Witt and Stuttgart. Wikipedia

Arenac County, Michigan.label: Arenac County
Arenac County, Michigan.description: Arenac County is a county in the U.S. state of Michigan. As of the 2010 census, the population was 17,269. The county seat is Standish. Wikipedia

Ashley County, Arkansas.label: Ashley County
Ashley County, Arkansas.description: Ashley County is a county located in the U.S. state of Arkansas, and was formed in 1848 from parts of Chicot, Drew and Union Counties. As of the 2010 census, the population was 21,853. The county seat is Hamburg. It is named for Chester Ashley. Wikipedia

Armstrong County, Texas.label: Armstrong County
Armstrong County, Texas.description: Armstrong County is a county located in the U.S. state of Texas. As of the 2010 census, the population was 1,901. Its county seat is Claude. Wikipedia

Aschaffenburg (district).label: Aschaffenburg
Aschaffenburg (district).description: Aschaffenburg is a district in Bavaria, Germany. It is bounded by the districts of Darmstadt-Dieburg, Offenbach, Main-Kinzig, the districts Main-Spessart and Miltenberg, and the town of Aschaffenburg. Wikipedia

Aschersleben-Staßfurt.label: Aschersleben-Staßfurt
Aschersleben-Staßfurt.description: Aschersleben-Staßfurt was a district in Saxony-Anhalt, Germany until 2007. It was bounded by the districts of Schönebeck, Bernburg, Mansfelder Land, Quedlinburg and Bördekreis. Wikipedia

Askøy.label: Askøy
Askøy.description: Askøy is a municipality in the county of Hordaland, Norway. Since the opening of the Askøy Bridge leading to the mainland in Bergen in 1992, the population has increased rapidly. Its population growth is as of 2008 among the highest in Norway. Wikipedia

Augsburg (district).label: Augsburg
Augsburg (district).description: Augsburg is a district in Bavaria, Germany. It is bounded by the city of Augsburg and the districts of Aichach-Friedberg, Landsberg, Ostallgäu, Unterallgäu, Günzburg, Dillingen and Donau-Ries. Wikipedia

Aure, Norway.label: Aure
Aure, Norway.description: Aure is a municipality in Møre og Romsdal county, Norway. It is part of the region of Nordmøre. The administrative centre is the village of Aure. Other villages in Aure include Gullstein, Stemshaug, Todalen, Tjeldbergodden, and Tømmervåg. Wikipedia

Attala County, Mississippi.label: Attala County
Attala County, Mississippi.description: Attala County is a county located in the U.S. state of Mississippi. As of the 2010 census, the population was 19,564. Its county seat is Kosciusko. Wikipedia

Austevoll.label: Austevoll
Austevoll.description: Austevoll is a municipality and an archipelago in the district of Midthordland in the county of Hordaland in Western Norway, Norway. Austevoll was separated from Sund on 1 January 1886. Wikipedia

Austrheim.label: Austrheim
Austrheim.description: Austrheim is a municipality in the county of Hordaland, Norway. Austrheim was separated from Lindås on 1 January 1910. Fedje was separated from Austrheim on 1 January 1947. The westernmost point of mainland Norway lies in the municipality. Wikipedia

Baden District, Austria.label: Baden District, Austria
Baden District, Austria.description: Bezirk Baden is a district of the state of Lower Austria in Austria. Wikipedia

Austin County, Texas.label: Austin County
Austin County, Texas.description: Austin County is a county in the U.S. state of Texas. As of the 2010 census, the population was 28,417. Its seat is Bellville. Wikipedia

Bærum.label: Bærum
Bærum.description: Bærum is a municipality in Akershus county, Norway. The administrative centre of the municipality is the town of Sandvika. Bærum was established as a municipality on 1 January 1838. A suburb of Oslo, Bærum is located on the west coast of the city. Wikipedia

Bad Doberan (district).label: Bad Doberan
Bad Doberan (district).description: Bad Doberan is a former district in Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Germany. It was named after its largest town, Bad Doberan, the German Bad meaning spa. Wikipedia

Avery County, North Carolina.label: Avery County
Avery County, North Carolina.description: Avery County is a county located in the U.S. state of North Carolina. As of the 2010 census, the population was 17,797. The county seat is Newland. Wikipedia

Baker County, Florida.label: Baker County
Baker County, Florida.description: Baker County is a county located in the U.S. state of Florida. As of the 2010 census, the population was 27,115. Its county seat is Macclenny, Florida. Wikipedia

Balestrand.label: Balestrand
Balestrand.description: Balestrand is a municipality in Sogn og Fjordane county, Norway. It is located on the northern shore of the Sognefjorden in the traditional district of Sogn. The administrative center is the village of Balestrand. Wikipedia

Balfouria.label: Balfouria
Balfouria.description: Balfouria is a moshav in northern Israel, south of Nazareth. Located near Afula, it falls under the jurisdiction of Jezreel Valley Regional Council. In 2006 it had a population of 312. Wikipedia

Ballangen.label: Ballangen
Ballangen.description: Ballangen is a municipality in Nordland county, Norway. It is part of the traditional district of Ofoten. The administrative centre of the municipality is the village of Ballangen. Wikipedia

Baker County, Georgia.label: Baker County
Baker County, Georgia.description:
Baker County is a county in the U.S. state of Georgia. As of the 2010 census, the population is 3,451. The county seat is Newton.
Baker County is included in the Albany, Georgia Metropolitan Statistical Area. Wikipedia

Balsfjord.label: Balsfjord
Balsfjord.description: Balsfjord is a municipality in Troms county, Norway. The administrative centre of the municipality is the village of Storsteinnes. Other villages include Mestervik, Mortenhals, and Nordkjosbotn. Wikipedia

Baltimore County, Maryland.label: Baltimore County
Baltimore County, Maryland.description: Baltimore County is a county located in the northern part of the U.S. state of Maryland. As of the 2010 census, the population was 805,029. Its county seat is Towson. Wikipedia

Baraga County, Michigan.label: Baraga County
Baraga County, Michigan.description: Baraga County is a county in the Upper peninsula in the U.S. state of Michigan. As of the 2010 census, the population was 8,860. The county seat is L'Anse. The county is named after Bishop Frederic Baraga. Wikipedia

Banner County, Nebraska.label: Banner County
Banner County, Nebraska.description: Banner County is a county located in the U.S. state of Nebraska. As of the 2010 census, the population was 690. Its county seat is Harrisburg; there are no incorporated municipalities within the county. Wikipedia

Barossa Valley.label: Barossa Valley
Barossa Valley.description: The Barossa Valley is one of Australia's oldest wine regions. Located in South Australia, the Barossa Valley is about 56 km northeast of the city of Adelaide. Wikipedia

Bastrop County, Texas.label: Bastrop County
Bastrop County, Texas.description: Bastrop County is a county located in the U.S. state of Texas. As of the 2010 census, the population was 74,171. Its county seat is Bastrop. Wikipedia

Barton County, Missouri.label: Barton County
Barton County, Missouri.description: Barton County is a county located in Southwest Missouri. As of the 2010 U.S. Census, the population was 12,402. Its county seat is Lamar. The county was organized in 1855 and named after U.S. Senator David Barton from Missouri. Wikipedia

Barren County, Kentucky.label: Barren County
Barren County, Kentucky.description: Barren County is a county located in the U.S. state of Kentucky. As of the 2010 census, the population was 42,173. Its county seat is Glasgow, Kentucky. The county was founded on December 20, 1798, from parts of Warren and Green Counties. Wikipedia

Bates County, Missouri.label: Bates County
Bates County, Missouri.description: Bates County is a county located in west central Missouri in the United States. As of the 2010 U.S. Census, the population was 17,049. Its county seat is Butler. Wikipedia

Bat Hadar.label: Bat Hadar
Bat Hadar.description:
Bat Hadar is a communal settlement in southern Israel. Located near Ashkelon, it falls under the jurisdiction of Hof Ashkelon Regional Council. In 2006 it had a population of 411.
The village was founded in 1994 by the regional council. Wikipedia

Bat Hefer.label: Bat Hefer
Bat Hefer.description:
Bat Hefer is an Israeli communal settlement in the Sharon plain, east of Netanya and adjacent to two kibbutzim; Bahan and Yad Hana.
Bat Hefer was originally founded as Sokho and named after that ancient town. Wikipedia

Bat Shlomo.label: Bat Shlomo
Bat Shlomo.description: Bat Shlomo is a moshav in northern Israel. Located on the southern slopes of Mount Carmel near Binyamina and Zikhron Ya'akov, it originally was built on 8068 dunams of land. It falls under the jurisdiction of Hof HaCarmel Regional Council. Wikipedia

Baxter County, Arkansas.label: Baxter County
Baxter County, Arkansas.description: Baxter County is a county located in the U.S. state of Arkansas. It is in the northern part of the state, and shares a border with Missouri. Wikipedia

Be'er Ora.label: Be'er Ora
Be'er Ora.description: Be'er Ora is a communal settlement near Eilat in the far south of Israel. It belongs to the Hevel Eilot Regional Council. It is located in the Arava region, just west of Highway 90, north of kibbutz Eilot, and south of Elifaz and Timna Park. Wikipedia

Batken Province.label: Batken Province
Batken Province.description: Batken Province is a province of Kyrgyzstan. Its capital is Batken. It is bounded on the east by Osh Province, on the south, west and north by Tajikistan and on the northeast by Uzbekistan. Wikipedia

Bayreuth (district).label: Bayreuth
Bayreuth (district).description: Bayreuth is a district in Bavaria, Germany. It surrounds, but does not include the city of Bayreuth. Wikipedia

Beaufort, Victoria.label: Beaufort
Beaufort, Victoria.description: Beaufort is a town in Victoria, Australia. It is located on the Western Highway midway between Ararat and Ballarat, in the Pyrenees Shire local government area. It is 387 metres above sea level. Wikipedia

Beaufort County, South Carolina.label: Beaufort County
Beaufort County, South Carolina.description: Beaufort County is a county in the U.S. state of South Carolina. As of the 2010 census, its population was 162,233. Its county seat is Beaufort. Wikipedia

Beaufort County, North Carolina.label: Beaufort County
Beaufort County, North Carolina.description: Beaufort County is a county located in the U.S. state of North Carolina. As of the 2010 Census, the population was 47,759. Its county seat is Washington. Wikipedia

Beadle County, South Dakota.label: Beadle County
Beadle County, South Dakota.description:
Beadle County is a county located in the State of South Dakota. As of the 2010 census, the population was 17,398. Its county seat is Huron.
Beadle County is the only county in the Huron Micropolitan Statistical Area. Wikipedia

Beit Arif.label: Beit Arif
Beit Arif.description: Beit Arif is a moshav in central Israel. Located near Shoham, it falls under the jurisdiction of Hevel Modi'in Regional Council. In 2006 it had a population of 724. Wikipedia

Beit Alfa.label: Beit Alfa
Beit Alfa.description: Beit Alfa is a kibbutz in the Northern District of Israel, near the Gilboa ridge. Wikipedia

Beit Ezra.label: Beit Ezra
Beit Ezra.description: Beit Ezra is a moshav in southern Israel. Located between Ashdod and Ashkelon on the Israeli coastal plain, it falls under the jurisdiction of Be'er Tuvia Regional Council. In 2006 it had a population of 962. Wikipedia

Beit Hagai.label: Beit Hagai
Beit Hagai.description: Beit Hagai is an Israeli settlement located in the southern Hebron hills in the West Bank. The settlement population was 460 in 2004, according to a classified government document published by the ... Wikipedia
